List Running Containers
(docker ps)

List All Containers (including stopped)
(docker ps -a)

Run a New Container
(docker run [OPTIONS] IMAGE [COMMAND] [ARG...]
   Example to run an interactive container:
   docker run -it ubuntu /bin/bash

Stop a Running Container
(docker stop CONTAINER_ID/NAME)

Start a Stopped Container
(docker start CONTAINER_ID/NAME)

Restart a Container
(docker restart CONTAINER_ID/NAME)

Remove a Container
(docker rm CONTAINER_ID/NAME)

Remove All Stopped Containers
(docker container prune)

Execute a Command in a Running Container
(docker exec -it CONTAINER_ID/NAME COMMAND)

Example to open a bash shell inside a running container:
(docker exec -it container_name /bin/bash)

View Container Logs
(docker logs CONTAINER_ID/NAME)

View Running Container Processes
(docker top CONTAINER_ID/NAME)

Show Container Stats
(docker stats)

2.Docker CLI Commands for Images

List Docker Images
(docker images)

Pull an Image from Docker Hub
(docker pull IMAGE_NAME)

Build an Image from a Dockerfile
(docker build -t IMAGE_NAME)

Remove an Image
(docker rmi IMAGE_ID/NAME)

Remove All Unused Images
(docker image prune)

3. Docker CLI Commands for Volumes

List Volumes
(docker volume ls)

Create a Volume
(docker volume create VOLUME_NAME)

Remove a Volume
(docker volume rm VOLUME_NAME)

Remove All Unused Volumes
(docker volume prune)

4. Docker CLI Commands for Networks

List Networks
(docker network ls)

Create a Network
(docker network create NETWORK_NAME)

Remove a Network
(docker network rm NETWORK_NAME)

5. Docker CLI Commands for Docker Compose

Start Docker Compose
(docker-compose up)

Stop Docker Compose
(docker-compose down)

Run in Detached Mode
(docker-compose up -d)

View Logs for Docker Compose
(docker-compose logs)

List Services in Docker Compose
(docker-compose ps)

Build the Services
(docker-compose build)

6. Docker System Commands

Check Docker Version
(docker --version)

Show Docker Info
(docker info)

Clean Up Unused Docker Resources (containers, networks, images, volumes)
(docker system prune)
